I have a Gaudralek. If I had a BoC/CHSD, etc. I'd use them too. As it is I have an Ichorflow, Trident of the Deep Sea, and Blade of Strategy that I often use depending on resists and the situation.<br>
<br>
Both 1H and 2H have a role. I'm much more likely to grab initial aggo with 1Hdrs. But with bigtime reposting mobs you really really want a 2hdr and Gaudralek holds aggro OK. But, if you aren't taunting and your 2hdr doesn't proc EB/TB, etc. you are not likely to steal aggro from the MT. In fact, I often use Gaudralek when I'm not the MT with very little problem.<br>
<br>
For those of you that are using Windblade, Blade of Strategy, Willsapper, etc. My advice would be that at best a Warrior does about 70% as much damage as a simularly equipped Rogue - damage alone will not get you aggro.<br>
<br>
For example, compare me and a Rogue each using Ichorflow and Trident of the Deep Sea. I might be doing 65 DPS while the Rogue is doing about 100 DPS. We are both doing the same procs. The only difference is that I am using my taunt macro ( and hopefully wearing a kick me buff ) while he shedding aggro as he is able.<br>
<br>
So, give taunt weapons a lot of thought and for goodness sake abandon the idea that DPS weapons are good aggro weapons. They aren't. The aggro situation for Warriors is pretty grim and it's going to take you EB/TB weapons, 2Hdrs, and a bagful of equipment, tricks, and experiance to do the job with the bigger mobs.<br>
<br>
BB<br>
Battleblade Burlydorf<br>
